blog.title: L'Echappée Belle d' Ygraïn
blog.description:
" Elle voulait une vie d'aventures, une vie folle, une vie plus grande qu'elle.Et l'on disait tout autour d'elle : [Ygraïn] rêve". Timothée de Fombelle, Victoria rêve

Je ne sais pas dessiner, les artworks que vous verrez ici ne sont pas les miens. Mais vous trouverez toujours un lien vers une gallerie de leurs auteurs. Personnellement, je ne fais que des montages (wallpaper, digiscrap, bannière ...) à partir de captures d'écran (screencap).. Ce tumblr est ma gallerie de rêves éphémères, mon échappée belle où je viens me ressourcer, me changer les idées, trouver un support à mes rêveries grâce aux fabuleux arts de d'autres artistes. .
Pour me contacter, en cas de problème: ygrain@gmail.com

Sinon: mon blog de lecture est: https://les-lectures-d-ygrain.tumblr.com/

summary: So my friends and I took a trip to Wales Comic Con this past weekend, which was all good. We live in London so it was nice to go...
body:
So my friends and I took a trip to Wales Comic Con this past weekend, which was all good. We live in London so it was nice to go somewhere different for a convention.

The thing about Wales Comic Con is that John Barrowman had been announced as a guest, before cancelling to go on I’m a Celebrity instead, so all day (without agreeing on it idk how the fuck it happened) whenever John Barrowman was mentioned we’d do the thing (like the gif below)

And this just became a thing that we did until we were in a fairly crowded corridor and John Barrowman came up so we went “BARROWMAN!” And all of a sudden there was a chorus of “BARROWMAN!” And it was the most beautiful thing I’ve ever experienced.

summary: Oooo I get more 11th doctor than 10th out of vices B.   Not the hugest fan of pftw musically. But he’s really grown into himself...
question: Oooo I get more 11th doctor than 10th out of vices B.   Not the hugest fan of pftw musically. But he’s really grown into himself personality-wise.
answer:
he looked like the 10th imo. now i’m gonna post pics where he looks like 10/david tennant

(n vices remains my fave music era for sure n prob my fave aesthetic era too. pftw is too commercial/by rote sometimes, even though i know that can be said about dancing’s not a crime n i love that song. n king of the clouds n dying n la are two of the best panic songs ever. kinky boots did so much good for him OMG. i love how he’s come into himself/what he’s developed into now. best bden yet.)

bonus tiny boy
